>> title: Baba Ganoush
>> cuisine: Middle Eastern
>> tags: snack, dip, vegan, gluten-free, soy-free
>> servings: 8
>> yield: 2 cups
>> storage_days: 5
>> storage_method: refrigerated
>> reheat: Serve cold.

== Char the Eggplants

Method 1 - Gas Flame: Place @eggplants{2%medium} directly over gas flame on stovetop. Turn with #tongs{} every few minutes, ~{10-15%minutes} total. Skin should be completely charred and flesh should be soft.

Method 2 - Broiler: Place eggplants on #sheet pan{}. Broil, turning every 5 minutes, ~{20%minutes} total until charred and collapsed.

== Make the Dip

Let eggplants cool slightly.

Cut in half and scoop flesh into #colander{}. Let drain ~{10%minutes} to remove bitterness.

Mash eggplant flesh with #fork{} in #bowl{} (or pulse briefly in food processor - don't over-blend).

Stir in @tahini{3%tbsp}, @fresh lemon juice{2%tbsp}, @garlic{2%cloves}(minced), @kosher salt{1/2%tsp}, and @olive oil{2%tbsp}.

Taste and adjust seasoning.

Transfer to #serving dish{}. Drizzle with @olive oil{1%tbsp}, sprinkle @smoked paprika{} and @fresh parsley{}(chopped).

Store in #airtight container{}.

-- Serve with: Pita bread, raw vegetables, crackers
